        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 3:22AM CDT by NWS Lake Charles LA</headline>
        <description>At 322 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from Holloway to near Turkey
Creek. Movement was east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to vegetation and outdoor
objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cottonport, Cheneyville, Mansura, Turkey Creek, Bunkie, Esler
Regional Airport, Lake Ophelia National Wildlife Refuge, Moreauville,
St. Landry, Forest Hill, Poland, Hessmer, Kolin, Ruby, Effie,
Holloway, Marksville, Deville, Libuse, and Echo.

This includes Interstate 49 between mile markers 46 and 74, and
between mile markers 80 and 81.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 AM CDT for
central and southwestern Louisiana.</instruction>
